				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Portugal (fan expansion for Age of Industry)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>This Portugal map has been primarily designed for 3 players (though also playable with 2 or even 4, though super tight) and features Portugal during the height of its industrial development (1855-65).  This map adds quite a few nuances to the base game such as:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;a.) Banks were hesitant to invest in the industrial sector so loans return $1 less for each additional loan after the first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;b.) Railway expansion was highly encouraged - certain rails are worth $4 at the end of the game instead of $2 and there are bonus VP for the player who finishes with the most VP.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;c.) Government debt was mounting rapidly due to poor management so to simulate this waste, corruption, and poor economy, there is always a region or industry where you CANNOT build.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;...and many more!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players must navigate the map's tightness - don't forget the option to combine both actions to build anywhere! - and suffocating economy to try and build a prosperous network.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
